The ratio between the height and the number of nickels is $6.25/100$.  Therefore, the ratio between the height of a stack of nickels and the number of nickels is $(6.25/100)\text{ in.} = 0.0625\text{ in.}$

There are $12$ inches in a foot, so the ratio is $0.0625\text{ in.} = (1/12)(0.0625)\text{ ft.}$

The height of an 8-foot stack is $8/(1/12)(0.0625) = 15360$ nickels.  At a rate of $5$ cents per nickel, the total value of the 8-foot stack is $15360(0.05)=768$ dollars.  Rounded to the nearest hundredth, this is $\boxed{768.00\text{ dollars}}$.
